# Markdown Editor with Live HTML Preview (Reflex)

## Background
Build a single-page Reflex application that gives the user a Markdown editing experience with a live HTML preview. The page is split into two columns: an editable Markdown source area on the left, and a live-updating HTML preview on the right. A toolbar above (or beside) the textarea offers `Bold`, `Italic`, and `Code` buttons that wrap the user's current text selection with the appropriate Markdown markers. A counter element shows the live word and character counts of the source.

The Markdown-to-HTML conversion must happen on the backend in a cached computed var, and the HTML must be injected into the page via `rx.html`.

## Requirements
- A Reflex project at `/home/user/myproject` initialized with `uv` (per the framework's recommended setup) and a Reflex app exposing a page at `/`.
- A single Reflex `State` subclass that owns at minimum:
  - `source: str` — the current Markdown source (controlled value of the textarea).
  - `selection_start: int` and `selection_end: int` — the cursor's current selection range inside the textarea, updated from a textarea event handler whenever the user changes the selection or types.
  - A cached computed var (decorated with `@rx.var(cache=True)`) named `preview_html` that converts `self.source` into HTML using the `markdown-it-py` library and returns the HTML string.
  - Cached computed vars (decorated with `@rx.var(cache=True)`) named `word_count` and `char_count` that return the number of words and the number of characters in `self.source`.
  - Event handlers `wrap_bold`, `wrap_italic`, and `wrap_code` that mutate `self.source` by wrapping the substring from `selection_start` to `selection_end` with the Markdown markers `**…**`, `*…*`, and `` `…` `` respectively. When the selection is empty (`selection_start == selection_end`), insert the marker pair at the cursor position so the cursor sits between the markers.
- The page layout must include the following DOM hooks (these IDs are how the verifier locates each piece):
  - A `<textarea>` element bound to `State.source` with the HTML id `md-source`.
  - A preview container element with HTML id `md-preview` whose inner HTML is produced by `rx.html(State.preview_html)`.
  - A counter element with HTML id `md-counter` whose displayed text follows the format `Words: <word_count> | Characters: <char_count>` (no other text in this element).
  - Three toolbar buttons with HTML ids `btn-bold`, `btn-italic`, and `btn-code` that trigger the corresponding wrap event handlers.
- The Markdown converter must be instantiated using `markdown-it-py`'s `MarkdownIt` class (any preset — `commonmark` is fine — as long as it produces standard HTML such as `<h1>`, `<p>`, `<strong>`, `<em>`, `<code>`, `<ul>`, `<li>` for the corresponding Markdown constructs).
- The preview must update reactively whenever the user edits the source.
- The application must not require any external network calls or external services to function.

## Implementation Hints
- Use `uv init`, `uv add reflex markdown-it-py`, then `uv run reflex init --template blank` to scaffold the project non-interactively, as described in the Reflex setup docs.
- The textarea's selection range can be captured by attaching an event handler to a native browser event (e.g. `on_select`, plus updating on `on_change` and `on_click`) and forwarding `event.target.selectionStart` / `event.target.selectionEnd` to the backend via Reflex's `EventHandler` argument-spec mechanism.
- Use Reflex's HTML-id passthrough (the `id` prop on Reflex components is forwarded as the DOM `id` attribute) to expose the stable selectors listed above.
- Render the converted HTML with `rx.html(State.preview_html)` placed inside a container whose `id` is `md-preview`.
- Make sure to set `value=State.source` and `on_change=State.set_source` (or a custom handler) on the textarea so it is fully controlled by state.
- A clean way to keep your computed var cached is to derive everything (preview, word count, character count) from `self.source` only; avoid touching `self.selection_start` / `self.selection_end` inside `preview_html` so caching is not invalidated by selection changes.
- See: Reflex computed vars (https://reflex.dev/docs/vars/computed-vars/), Reflex rx.html (https://reflex.dev/docs/library/other/html-embed/), Reflex events overview (https://reflex.dev/docs/events/events-overview/), markdown-it-py docs (https://markdown-it-py.readthedocs.io/en/latest/using.html).

## Acceptance Criteria
- Project path: `/home/user/myproject`
- Start command: `cd /home/user/myproject && uv run reflex run --env prod --loglevel info`
- Frontend port: `3000`
- Backend port: `8000`
- Route under test: `/` (i.e. `http://localhost:3000/`)
- Required stable DOM ids on the page: `md-source` (textarea), `md-preview` (HTML preview container), `md-counter` (counter element), `btn-bold`, `btn-italic`, `btn-code` (toolbar buttons).
- Counter element text must follow the exact format `Words: <N> | Characters: <M>` (single space around the pipe).
- Markdown rendering behavior (tested via the live preview's inner HTML):
  - A heading source (e.g. `# Heading`) must produce an `<h1>` element containing the heading text inside `#md-preview`.
  - Strong emphasis source (e.g. `**bold**`) must produce a `<strong>` element with the text inside `#md-preview`.
  - Emphasis source (e.g. `*italic*`) must produce an `<em>` element with the text inside `#md-preview`.
  - Inline code source (e.g. `` `code` ``) must produce a `<code>` element with the text inside `#md-preview`.
  - Unordered list source (e.g. `- a` / `- b`) must produce a `<ul>` containing two `<li>` elements with the corresponding text.
- Toolbar mutation behavior on the controlled textarea:
  - With source `hello world`, the user selecting characters `[0, 5)` (the word `hello`) and clicking `#btn-bold` must result in a source value of `**hello** world`.
  - With the same `hello world` source, selecting `[6, 11)` and clicking `#btn-italic` must result in `hello *world*`.
  - With source `print(x)`, selecting `[0, 8)` and clicking `#btn-code` must result in `` `print(x)` ``.
  - With an empty selection (caret at end of `abc`, i.e. `selection_start == selection_end == 3`) clicking `#btn-bold` must result in `abc****`.
- Counter behavior on the textarea value `the quick brown fox` must show `Words: 4 | Characters: 19`; on the empty string it must show `Words: 0 | Characters: 0`.
- The Markdown → HTML conversion must be implemented as a cached computed var. The application source code under `/home/user/myproject` must contain at least one occurrence of `@rx.var(cache=True)` (or `@reflex.var(cache=True)`) annotating the preview computed var.
- A `requirements.txt` (or equivalent dependency manifest used by `uv`) inside the project must declare the `markdown-it-py` dependency.
- Background processes started during the task must be terminated before completion: no orphan `reflex run`, `next` / `node`, or backend processes may remain after the executor finishes.


